This paper deals with learning sensorimotor control policies for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques, such as convolutional neural networks, and uses weakly labeled image data, which suggests that it could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves multitask learning and attentional mechanisms, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of generalization, which is a common issue in control systems and robotics (cs.SY).
